\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 And, uh, for those technical team in the room, I want to highlight that.\cb1 \
\cb3 AI agent is what we call technically as a heuristic system, which is basically the nature of generative AI, where it uses the probabilistic model to identify, extract, classify, process.\cb1 \
\cb3 data set that coming in. There's a pro and con of this system. We all know that generative AI these days is the good stuff. That's why we're all here. But there's a draw side of the nature of the heuristic system as well.\cb1 \
\cb3 Uh\'85 for example, everyone keeps\'85 always asks me that, Kun Suruj, how do we build a system where you run the system twice and it gives you the same result? The answer is no, you can't expect\'85 you cannot expect that from a generative AI system.\cb1 \
\cb3 If you expect consistency, you need to have another system baked into the same solution. Another system is what we call deterministic system. So basically, it's a system where there is no randomness. One plus one is two. Three plus four is seven.\cb1 \
\cb3 as always, it's going to be fully predictable behavior, there's no random, it's pretty much rule-based. And guess what? Everyone knows this as Python.\cb1 \
\cb3 So my point is, when you design your system from an engineering standpoint.\cb1 \
\cb3 Don't only use prompt, because if you only use prompt and you say, hey, let Claude Cowork do this, let Copilot Studio do that, you're going to end up to have so many randomness in the system, and eventually you can't scale it out.\cb1 \
\cb3 So you need to think about which part of my workflow is going to be heuristic, and which part of my workflow has to be deterministic.\cb1 \
\cb3 Because any part that you expect consistency, repeatability, you need to have a deterministic system, rule-based system, not a heuristic system. On the other hand, if that part of your workflow require.\cb1 \
\cb3 you know, some nuances of legal interpretation, language differences, you're gonna need to rely on heuristic system, not Python.\cb1 \
\cb3 Think about how to identify five different ways to say data privacy versus if you want to do a calculation, don't use LLM to calculate for you. You can simply write Python for three lines of Python. You can do the calculation much simpler.\cb1 \
\cb3 Okay? So that would be my very, very strong recommendation when designing the system. Another one, and I intentionally put this in a funny way, the governance. So everyone talk a lot about how to govern AI, how to automate, how not to automate.\cb1 \
\cb3 Where do you put human in the loop? Uh, my response to that is, there's no\'85 there's no\'85\cb1 \
\cb3 There's no single answer to all those questions. It all depends on the project, it all depends on how you design the workflow, and it all depends on how you interact with the user.\cb1 \
\cb3 I think it's more of an art than a science. For example.\cb1 \
\cb3 anyone who watched football like me would remember this photo. This is\'85 for those of you who\'85 who don't watch football, I'm sorry. Uh, but this is the scene of what we call the hand of God.\cb1 \
\cb3 where Diego Maradona just uh do uh did the handball uh back in those days in the football field there is no what we call WA the video uh uh referee so the referee did not catch that eventually that handball was.\cb1 \
\cb3 accepted uh uh and eventually uh Argentina got that score uh got that score this is a case of back at those day in the football in the game of football there is no oversight which mean there's no friction every every uh movement every turn.\cb1 \
\cb3 All the games are played quite continuously.\cb1 \
\cb3 But for those of you who watch football these days, we have video.\cb1 \
\cb3 And the video, it has pinpoint just like a small fraction of the upside of the players. So it turns out that these day in football game, we have so many oversight, lots of friction, there's less automation.\cb1 \
\cb3 So, in your system, when you pick up, you know, how much automation that I should put in, or how much oversight I should put in, think about these two extreme scenarios. No oversight is bad, but too much oversight is also bad as well.\cb1 \
\cb3 Uh, so you need to find the right balance. I think that's\'85 that's what I'm trying to convey with this scenario.\cb1 \
\cb3 Lastly, I have sum up five key principle when designing a generative AI system, at least from my experience dealing with legal tech and lots of regulation.\cb1 \
\cb3 Uh, number one, I think most of you technical people in the room would already know this.\cb1 \
